subSubSection.paragraph:
Locality not specified :
3 ♂♂, 3 ♀♀, “ Styria ”, “Styr.”, etc., leg. Pipitz, etc. ( MNB , NHMW );
1 ♀, “Silesia” ( MNB )
;
2 ♂♂, 1 ♀, “Kaukas, Leder” ( NHMW , cAss)
.

Abdomen approximately as broad as elytra in specimens with short elytra and narrower than elytra in specimens with long elytra; punctation denser and coarser in anterior than in posterior portions of tergites; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII (
Figs 4–9
) usually broadly and weakly, rarely deeply concave, with unmodified long marginal setae, in postero-lateral portions with dense long and thin setae.
